## When this applies

If the user (or task) touches **design, UI, UX, visuals, layout, typography, motion, color, copy, accessibility, or “make it look better”** — treat it as a design task. Do **not** improvise generic UI: use the routing below and **read the relevant `SKILL.md` file(s)** at `.agents/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md` **before** editing components or giving design review.

Skills come from the [Impeccable](https://impeccable.style/) skill pack (plus project-specific entries). Multiple skills may apply; read all that fit (e.g. **frontend-design** + **arrange** for a new layout-heavy screen).

## Routing (intent → skill folder)

| User / task intent | Skill folder |
| --- | --- |
| New screen, component, or substantial UI build; overall design direction | `frontend-design` |
| Responsive breakpoints, mobile/tablet, touch targets, viewport | `adapt` |
| Animation, transitions, micro-interactions, motion | `animate` |
| Layout, spacing, rhythm, alignment, visual hierarchy, crowded UI | `arrange` |
| Accessibility / performance / theming / anti-patterns audit, scored review | `audit` |
| Bland, generic, safe, needs more character (without breaking usability) | `bolder` |
| Labels, errors, microcopy, confusing text | `clarify` |
| Too gray, needs palette / warmth / color | `colorize` |
| UX/design review, evaluation, feedback on a design | `critique` |
| Personality, delight, memorable touches | `delight` |
| Simplify, declutter, remove noise | `distill` |
| Extract components, tokens, design-system style reuse | `extract` |
| Edge cases, overflow, i18n, production hardening | `harden` |
| Drift from design system, inconsistent spacing/tokens | `normalize` |
| Onboarding, empty states, first-run | `onboard` |
| Slow, janky, bundle, performance | `optimize` |
| Ambitious effects (high effort / “wow”) | `overdrive` |
| Final pass, alignment, shipping polish | `polish` |
| Too loud, overwhelming, tone down | `quieter` |
| Fonts, type scale, readability, hierarchy | `typeset` |
| One-time design context for the repo | `teach-impeccable` |
| Domain terminology / glossary (not visual design) | `ubiquitous-language` |
| Industrial product-design lens (Score Slate) | Prefer `internal/AI Prompts/AI UI Industrial Reviewer.md` together with `critique` or `audit` when reviewing UI |

## Procedure

1. Match intents from the table (and synonyms).
2. **Read** `SKILL.md` for each selected skill (full path: `.agents/skills/<folder>/SKILL.md`).
3. Implement or review **following** that skill; default project stack rules (Vue SFCs, Tailwind, etc.) still apply from `core.mdc`.

If nothing matches, start with **`frontend-design`** for build work or **`critique`** for review work.
